    "Exposing directly via service-based interfaces (SBIs) can eliminate redundant peer-to-peer (P2P) interface definitions and unnecessary access and mobility management function (AMF) transparent forwarding, thereby enhancing communication efficiency.",
    "The evolution of service-based RANs is generally categorized into two phases: introduction of SBIs and service definition and on-demand combination (Li N et al., 2022b), as shown in Fig. 11.",
    "SBIs can be divided into partially service-based N2 interface (option 1) and fully service-based N2 interface (option 2).",
    "It can also include the openness of interfaces such as E1/F1.",
    "These two interfaces can share a phased evolution relationship, such as evolving from option 1 to option 2, or a parallel selection relationship."
